🕒 We are proposing to end seasonal clock changes in Europe in 2019.
The last mandatory change to summertime would take place on Sunday 31 March 2019. 
#SOTEU #ClockChange #EfficientEU https://t.co/amp3k6ciui

We want to stop clock-changing. 🕒
Member States should themselves decide whether their citizens live in summer or winter time.

Press conference by Vice-President @MarosSefcovic and Commissioner @Bulc_EU #SOTEU #EfficientEU https://t.co/tndKFoDCkn

We need to protect elections, campaigns, political parties and candidates from cyberattacks.
We propose to create a European Competence Centre to better target and coordinate available funding for cybersecurity cooperation.
→ https://t.co/zl0OeHaTAO #SOTEU #EUprotects https://t.co/PbYN5Q4Q9E

Political parties are increasingly using personal data to target citizens online. 
We are thus giving guidance on how all actors involved in elections need to abide by the new #GDPR EU data protection rules.
#SOTEU #EUelections2019 #EUprotects ↓ https://t.co/o7fvBok3Nf

Recent revelations have shown risks for citizens to have their data misused and be targeted by mass online disinformation campaigns.
We propose sanctions for the illegal use of personal data to deliberately influence elections.
→ https://t.co/OK61RmqMeZ #SOTEU #EUelections2019 https://t.co/UqDDGYKW67

To ensure that Europeans are able to make their political choices next May in fair and secure elections, our new set of measures focus on:
🛡️Data protection
🔍Transparency
🔐Cybersecurity
🌐Cooperation
⚖️Appropriate sanctions
#SOTEU #EUelections2019
More in our factsheet ↓ https://t.co/z1NCPDSyQy

The next #EUelections2019 will take place in May.
We propose new rules to ensure that they are organised in a free and fair manner, and to better protect them from manipulation by third countries or private interests.
→ https://t.co/OK61RmqMeZ #SOTEU #EUprotects https://t.co/VsPeen3obG

We need an EU that protects our free and fair elections, and we also need to counter terrorism online and offline.

Press conference by @VeraJourova @JKingEU @GabrielMariya 
#SOTEU #EUprotects #EUelections2019 https://t.co/OEMs98fzXZ

We are renewing our call to open safe and legal pathways to Europe pathways to the Union. We need skilled migrants.

We are proposing to reinforce the European Union Agency for Asylum to help Member States to process asylum applications swiftly, including through the deployment of migration management support teams. #MigrationEU
#SOTEU https://t.co/GRRv5OTDwi

We are proposing to equip the #EUBorderGuard with the operational capacity and powers needed to effectively support Member States on the ground.
The new standing corps of 10,000 operational staff will ensure that the EU has the necessary capabilities in place.
#SOTEU #MigrationEU https://t.co/dFR50nM3CL
